Boil a full #kettle{}.

While it boils, peel and grate the @garlic clove{2} (or use a #garlic press{}).

Heat a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat (no oil).

Once hot, add the @lamb mince{200%g} and @sliced mushrooms{80%g}. Cook until browned, ~{6-7%minutes}.

Use #spoon{} to break the mince up as it cooks, then drain and discard any excess fat. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw mince. It's cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Meanwhile, pour the boiled water into a large #saucepan{} with @salt{1/2%tsp} and bring back to the boil.

When boiling, add the @rigatoni pasta{180%g} to the water and bring back to the boil. Cook until tender, ~{12%minutes}.

Once cooked, drain in a #colander{} and pop back in the pan. Drizzle with @oil{} and stir through to stop it sticking together.

Add the garlic, @gochujang paste{50%g} (add less if you'd prefer things milder) and @tomato puree{30%g} to the mince. Stir-fry until fragrant, ~{1%minute}.

Stir the @creme fraiche{75%g}, @chicken stock paste{10%g}, @sugar{1%tsp} and @water for the sauce{100%ml} into the frying pan.

Simmer until thickened slightly, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Stir the cooked pasta through the sauce until well combined. Taste the sauce and season with @salt{} and @pepper{} if needed.

Share the lamb rigatoni between your #bowls{}.

Sprinkle over the @grated hard Italian style cheese{20%g} to finish. Enjoy!